# Architecture Rules

- instrument-core must NEVER import tauri, wasm-bindgen, tokio, or std::fs
- All Rust logic in instrument-core must be pure functions — no side effects
- All React components call src/bridge/index.ts only — never invoke() directly
- Platform detection uses "__TAURI_INTERNALS__" in window (Tauri v2)
- Every new tool must have an entry in src/registry/index.ts
- Tool components are always lazy-loaded via React.lazy()
- src/constants/library.ts is the source of truth for category/role mappings
- Use pnpm for all package operations — never npm or yarn
- pnpm add for dependencies, pnpm add -D for dev, pnpm dlx for one-off CLIs
- Every tool must have a corresponding doc in docs/tools/<tool-name>.md
- Inline comments explain WHY not WHAT
